Prophet.Commentary: I do set My bow in the cloud, and it shall be for a token of a covenant between Me and the earth (Genesis 9:13). The bow shall be in the cloud; and I will look upon it, that I may remember the everlasting covenant between God and every living creature of all flesh that is upon the earth (Genesis 9:16). As the appearance of the bow that is in the cloud in the day of rain, so was the appearance of the brightness round about. This was the appearance of the likeness of the glory of the LORD. And when I saw it, I fell upon my face, and I heard a voice of one that spoke (Ezekiel 1:28).
